args: All right, everybody! One more time!\nHAAAAPPY NEW YEAR!
I find myself growing used to this little\ncustom of ours. It feels good to cry out\nsuch things to ring in a new year.
Ever since Ieyasu taught us about it,\nNew Year's has become the event ain't\nNOBODY wants to miss!
Probably because of all the food,\nwhich makes it the BEST holiday!
I had Mitsuba teach me how to make an\nauthentic Hinomotoan New Year's meal,\nso please eat to your hearts' content.

So I love you, Cleo, and your cooking is
hotter than a flaming rock in a catapult...
but right now I just wanna play some
New Year's games!

That's a great idea, Notte! We could play
hanetsuki, fly some kites, spin tops...
Oh, or even try that Hinomotoan poetry
game again!
We've learned so many things now,\nso what do you want to play?
Y'know, now that you actually put it to me,\nI'm kinda stuck. I mean, we've done all\nthose already, you know?
They're super fun and all, but there's just\nno surprise to 'em anymore. No OOMPH.\nThat's a word, right? Oomph?
Howdy, pardners! Y'all mind if we crash\nthis here hootenanny with ya?
Sure as shootin'! It's been a hot minute,\nhuh? Hope y'all are havin' a real swell\nNew Year.
Assistant to Seimei, Leader of the Ox Clan\nKuzunoha
It appears you have already begun\nyour New Year's feast.
Onmyoji and Leader of the Ox Clan\nSeimei
Ohmigosh, it's Kuzunoha AND Seimei!\nOh man, this is so great! ...Er, but wait.\nWhat are you doing here?
We had some business 'round these parts,\nso Lord Seimei said we outta pop in and\nsay yee-haw.
This was SEIMEI'S idea? Wow. I figured\nhe would view this kind of thing as a\nbig ol' pain in the... Well, as a pain.
Oh, normally he ain't much for shindigs\nand whatnot, but he makes himself a\nright special exception for New Year's.
He always had himself a real humdinger of\na time spendin' New Year's with his late\ngrandpappy, so now he cherishes it.
Yes, I remember how much care he took\nrunning the tournament last year, as well\nas planning the banquet.
Right ya are! So anyway, he was wonderin'\nwhat y'all were gettin' up to—YEOWCH!
You're running your mouth, stupid fox.\n...Yes, well, that's enough out of her.\nAre you all enjoying the New Year?
Heck yeah we are! There's tons of food,\nand we were just talking about what\ngame to play. Er, but...
We're kinda used to all the games we've\nlearned, so they may be a little lacking\nin excitement, you know?
Hey, do YOU guys know any other games?!\nI wanna try something like nothing we've\ntried before!
Ya want somethin' that'll knock your socks\noff in a brand new way?
Well, hold on to yer slop buckets, 'cause I\ngot me a whopper of a game!
It's m'own special-made, real-life\nsugoroku board game! TAAA-DAAAAH!
Uh...that just looks like a box.
That IS what it looks like, ain't it?\nBut it's actually a special game set\nI made with one'a Lord Seimei's spells.
I knew Lord Seimei wanted everyone to\nhave an extra-special New Year's, so I\nmade it happen with this here game.
This lil' feller is a heap'a fun no matter\nhow many times ya play it! And I know,\n'cause I used my whole holiday to make it.
You wasted your entire holiday\nmaking that...thing?
I sure as heck did—and I guarantee ya\nwon't have fun like this nowhere else!\nSo whatcha say? Interested?
I sure am! But, um...if I remember how\nsugoroku works, I can't just play it by\nmyself, right?
I'd love to give it a shot if that's all right.\nDoes anyone else want in?
The more the merrier is usually the rule of\nthumb for any game, so count me in.
If my ol' pranking buddy Kuzunoha is\ninvolved, you KNOW I ain't missing this!
And it ain't a party OR a game until Ranzal\nshows up, so consider Ranzal showed!
I would like to join as well. Is it possible\nto play this particular game with six?
Heck yeah, it is! Y'all get ready and enjoy\nyerselves, and I'll be out here cheerin' ya\non the whole durn way!
Uh, did she just say ＂out here＂?
Right then! Lemme just make the six of\nya the target of this here spell...
O that which glimmers as the moon! May\nyer light become joy and open the gate\nto the world of dreams! ONMYO!
Huh? Wait, I'm getting sucked in!\nNoooooo, I don't wanna play anymooore!
I think we're fine, Notte—I'm honestly\nmore concerned with the ground.
The ground? ...Oh, I see! It reads ＂START＂\nthere in some very flashy colors.
There's squares as far as the eye can see,\nand they all have stuff written on 'em.
But that means this place is...
You bet yer sweet bippy it is! Y'all are\nstandin' in the world of my real-life\nsugoroku board game!
AAAHHH! KUZUNOHA'S IN THE SKY!\nIs THIS what you meant when you said\nit was ＂real life＂?!

I meant y'all were gonna be the pieces!
For this game, ya gotta make yer way
through the world and have yerself some
real-life experiences.
Oh, but don't get yer overalls in a bunch,\n'cause I made sure there was a way for\ny'all to all come home. Lemme show ya!
Well, cow plop! That ain't how it's\nsupposed to go! I coulda sworn I did\nthat there spell right. Unless... OH NO!

So, um, I'm right sorry 'bout this, y'all,
but I sorta screwed up the spell, which
means ya can't leave unless ya go
and beat the game.
You mean we're TRAPPED in here?!
Yeah, and I'm real sorry about it! If ya\nmanage to make it out alive, I'll definitely\nfind a way what to make it up to ya.
Enough, you stupid fox. If all they have to\ndo to escape is finish the game, then we\nwill simply help them finish.
Right then, all of you. Hurry up and finish,\nthen return here. If you need help, I will\ndo whatever I can.
Okay, I feel WAY better knowing that\nSeimei's helping us, so let's go out\nthere and beat this thing like a rug!
And, um, maybe we can have some fun\nwhile we're at it? Pretty please with\nliterally everything on top of it?
Notte's right. It's not every day you get\nto play a game like this, so we might as\nwell enjoy the experience.
See? He gets me. Now let's get this\nparty started! Ready...set...GOOOO!
